{"key":"processedPost-10016925","value":{"id":10016925,"first":10013700,"last":10017453,"when":1237694422,"utime":"03/22/09 07:00 AM","cleanedPost":"Actually, plain rye DOES require a casing layer.&nbsp; You don't need to wait a week after full colonization to use your spawn.&nbsp; It's a good idea to wait a week after full colonization of fruiting substrates because it leads to a better and more even flush.&nbsp; The mycelium needs time to consolidate its hold on the substrate.&nbsp; That only means waiting from a few days to a week with cubensis, and a whole month after full colonization for shiitake.&nbsp; If you expose to fruiting conditions early, it's a major cause of mutants and poor flushing performance.<br />RR"}}